race.comment: Impossible to tip against unbeaten mare TENNESSEE BOUND (4) who backed up her fast maiden win at Kyneton with a dominant performance in a BM62 at Cranbourne, leading throughout in very slick time to go on and win by five lengths. Drawn the inside, she should bounce straight to the top and win again. ESCARPA (8) was unsuited getting back in the small field second up at Geelong having won well there fresh. She can be hitting the line strongly at big odds. NEPRAVDA (7) is going well without winning this time in, good on heavy ground at Kyneton last time out. She can get a nice run here and challenge for a placing. CANARA (10) resumes. She may need a bit further but can be hitting the line.
